#
# Per-rig overrides for the input subprocess.
#
# Sourced from config/inputconf.tcl AFTER the built-in known-device table
# is seeded (wch / ILITEK / eGalax touchscreens) and BEFORE
# inputAutodiscover runs. So local entries override the defaults
# (last-match-wins) and new entries added here are visible to discovery.
#
# On a rig with only the standard known hardware attached, this file is
# not needed — autodiscover just works. Use it to:
#
#   - declare what devices this rig must have (inputExpect)
#   - teach the module about new hardware (inputKnownDevice)
#   - override a default rotation or screen size per-rig
#

# --- Expectations ------------------------------------------------------
#
# By default, startup is permissive: missing devices are ignored.
# Declaring `inputExpect` makes the rig fail loudly at startup if the
# class has no matched device. `-optional` is available if you want the
# declaration for documentation / diagnostics but no enforcement.
#
# inputExpect touchscreen
# inputExpect trackpad
# inputExpect trackpad -optional

# --- Teaching the module about new hardware ----------------------------
#
# Touchscreens: must provide screen_w and screen_h. Match against the
# /dev/input/by-id/<name> basename (Tcl glob) or the libevdev-reported
# device name.
#
# inputKnownDevice touchscreen *MyNewPanel_USB_1024x600* \
#     -screen_w 1024 -screen_h 600
#
# Options:
#   -screen_w W       pixel width of the display this panel covers
#   -screen_h H       pixel height
#   -rotation N       0 / 90 / 180 / 270 (default -1 = auto-detect from
#                     /proc/cmdline's video=HDMI-A-1:...:rotate=N)
#   -track_drag 0|1   emit DRAG events on movement while active
#                     (default 0: only PRESS and RELEASE)
#   -hdmi_output name HDMI connector name for rotation detection
#                     (default HDMI-A-1)

# --- Overriding a built-in default -------------------------------------
#
# To override the built-in defaults for a known panel on this specific
# rig (e.g. this ILITEK is mounted rotated), re-declare the same pattern
# with different values. Last-match-wins.
#
# inputKnownDevice touchscreen *ILITEK_ILITEK-TP* \
#     -screen_w 1280 -screen_h 800 -rotation 180

# --- Debugging discovery -----------------------------------------------
#
# inputProbe enumerates every /dev/input/event* with identifiers, the
# classifier's verdict, and capability bits. Invoke on demand:
#
#   send input "inputProbe"
#
# Or at startup by setting DSERV_INPUT_PROBE=1 in the environment / unit.
